# OpenSpec (bundle maintainer)

**Canonical overlay:** [openspec-git-integration.md](../../overlays/lsi/docs/workflows/openspec-git-integration.md)

Tracked changes: **`openspec/changes/<change-slug>/`**

Config: [openspec/config.yaml](../../openspec/config.yaml)

**Branch policy:** [local-branch-workflow.mdc](local-branch-workflow.mdc)

## Workflow commands

Installed under `.cursor/commands/` (gitignored) by `./snippets/bootstrap-maintainer-local.sh`.

**OpenSpec:** `/opsx:explore`, `/opsx:propose`, `/opsx:apply`, `/opsx:sync`, `/opsx:archive`

**LSI (git):** `/lsi:card`, `/lsi:branch`, `/lsi:commit`, `/lsi:pr`, `/lsi:close`, etc.

| Step | Command |
|------|---------|
| Explore | `/opsx:explore` |
| Propose | `/opsx:propose` |
| Implement | `/opsx:apply` |
| Commit | `/lsi:commit` (when asked) |
| Close on main | `/lsi:close` after merge |

## Before implementation

1. Read `openspec/changes/<slug>/proposal.md`, `design.md`, `tasks.md`.
2. **`tasks.md` must not** list `/opsx:sync`, `/opsx:archive`, or `/lsi:close` as apply deliverables.

## Commits

- Only `git commit` when the user explicitly asks.
- Commit `openspec/` changes with implementation PRs.
